# Feature Updates: Persist "Perfect Day" Status

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> This change ensures that once you achieve a "Perfect Day" (all habits completed), it stays counted even if you reset the day to start over. The "Perfect Day" count will be a combination of your current habit history AND a separate log of days you've already mastered.

## Proposed Changes

### Logic & State Management
#### [MODIFY] [App.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/스위치웹서비스/daily-habit-tracker/src/App.jsx)
- **Add State**: `perfectDayLog` (array of date strings), initialized from `localStorage`.
- **Update Effect**: Persist `perfectDayLog` to `localStorage` whenever it changes.
- **Update [resetDailyProgress](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%8A%A4%EC%9C%84%EC%B9%98%EC%9B%B9%EC%84%9C%EB%B9%84%EC%8A%A4/daily-habit-tracker/src/App.jsx#97-105)**:
    - Before resetting history, add the current `today` date to `perfectDayLog` if it isn't already there.
    - Pass `perfectDayLog` to [Profile](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%8A%A4%EC%9C%84%EC%B9%98%EC%9B%B9%EC%84%9C%EB%B9%84%EC%8A%A4/daily-habit-tracker/src/Profile.jsx#5-270) and [Stats](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%8A%A4%EC%9C%84%EC%B9%98%EC%9B%B9%EC%84%9C%EB%B9%84%EC%8A%A4/daily-habit-tracker/src/Stats.jsx#4-68) components as a prop.

#### [MODIFY] [utils.js](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/스위치웹서비스/daily-habit-tracker/src/utils.js)
- **Update [calculatePerfectDays](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%8A%A4%EC%9C%84%EC%B9%98%EC%9B%B9%EC%84%9C%EB%B9%84%EC%8A%A4/daily-habit-tracker/src/utils.js#60-77)**:
    - Accept a second argument: `perfectDayLog`.
    - Logic:
